    {
      "id": "57070816_84290460",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/platform/components/oom-cert-service/Makefile",
      "patchset_number": 16,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "It's good idea, unfortunately I don't know how to do it. \nThe catalog we mount on container, gets permissions user/group 10001/10001, but I don't know where it's coming from. We can user 10001 user, so it works on CI, but then it won't work on local environments, because occures only on CI environment.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3771,
        "name": "Adam Wudzinski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "adam.wudzinski@nokia.com",
        "username": "adamwudzinski"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-20 12:51:35.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9240a78c_e71807d8",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "f06ca7ad_756ead2e",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/platform/components/oom-cert-service/Makefile",
      "patchset_number": 16,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "Just to clarify my previous message. Catalog gets these permissions (10001) only on CI, not on local environment. \n\nI suspected that host permissions are propagated, however it doesn't occur locally.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3771,
        "name": "Adam Wudzinski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "adam.wudzinski@nokia.com",
        "username": "adamwudzinski"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-20 12:54:01.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "57070816_84290460",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "57292f3f_2b751722",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/platform/components/oom-cert-service/Makefile",
      "patchset_number": 16,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "You are right. Permissions gets propagated so in that case I'd basically run the container as the same user who is executing this makefile\n\n--user `whoami`\n\nand it should be fine",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-20 13:28:48.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f06ca7ad_756ead2e",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "42cc7b81_b269b90f",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/platform/components/oom-cert-service/Makefile",
      "patchset_number": 16,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "OK I tried this. \nIt will probably work on CI, but when I run it locally permissions do not propagate, thus owner of mounted folder is 'onap' and user on my host is 'adam'. When I run I got an error, because there is no such user on the container.\n\nSo the problem now is that on CI permissions propagate and locally they do not.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3771,
        "name": "Adam Wudzinski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "adam.wudzinski@nokia.com",
        "username": "adamwudzinski"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-20 13:56:01.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "57292f3f_2b751722",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "bd5eba2d_49fba831",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/platform/components/oom-cert-service/Makefile",
      "patchset_number": 16,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "Could you check also --user $(id -u):$(id -g)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
